718978f-a.text:
Claremont Avenue, west side (buildings there upon), from W.116th Street and Riverside Drive (left) to a point on a line with W. 118th Street, showing apartment structures formerly occupied by Barnard College students and that now house the faculty. They are, from left to right, the Paterno, the dual Barnard Court, the Sophomore, the 11 story Peter Minuit and Eton Hall. The photographer is viewing westward from Broadway and across the fenced lot where the present (in 1938) Barnard College Students Building stands.
October 1914.
Geo. L. Bulgue
